  <front>
   <head>SONNET TO A ROBIN-RED-BREAST.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">DEAR, social bird, that oft with fearless love</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Giv'st thy soft form to man's protective care,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Pleas'd, when rude tempests vex the ruffled air,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For the warm roof to leave the naked grove.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Kindest, and last of Summer's tuneful train,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ah! do not yet give o'er thy plaintive lay,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But charm mild Zephyr to a longer stay,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And oft renew thy sweetly-parting strain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So when rough Winter frowns with brow severe,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And chilling blasts shall strip the sheltering trees;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When meagre Want that shivering frame shall seize,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Death, with dart uplifted, hover near;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">My grateful hand the liberal crumbs shall give,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">My bosom warm thee, and my kiss revive.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
